eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarm
Reference wind farm metadata.
Attributes: reference_wind_farm_id (str): Unique ID for the reference wind farm within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. wind_farm_configuration (WindFarmConfiguration): The configuration data for the reference wind farm. datasets (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataset]): Metadata for the operational dataset.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataset
Reference wind farm operational dataset metadata.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Label of the reference wind farm dataset. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. data_supplier_organisation (Organisation): The organisation that supplied the data. data_type (OperationalDataType(StrEnum)): The type of data in the operational data, categorised as 'scada' for data from a Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) system, 'metered' for data from a production meter, 'environmental_measurement' for data from an (on-site) environmental measurement station such as a meteorological mast or a remote sensing device (RSD) and 'other' for any other type of unit. data_source_type (DataSourceType(StrEnum)): The type of the operational data source. Primary data, such as primary SCADA data, comes directly from the source without processing. Report data refers to data extracted from report document, such as monthly operational reports. Other secondary data comprises all other data source categories, such as secondary SCADA data provided in processed (harmonised) form by a data management service provider. used_data_variables (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable]): A list of the types of data variables included in this dataset and used in the assessment. For a large dataset (such as a full wind turbine SCADA dataset) this field should not include all the variables but only the ones that were used in the analysis. time_resolution (TimeResolution(StrEnum)): Time resolution of the data. data_period_start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_period_end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.WindFarmConfiguration
A collection of wind turbines considered as one unit (plant).
Attributes: name (str): Name of the wind farm. label (Optional[str]): Abbreviated label of the wind farm. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. turbines (list[TurbineConfiguration]): List of specifications for constituent turbines. relevance (WindFarmRelevance(StrEnum)): The relevance of the wind farm for the assessment. operational_lifetime_start_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime start date (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None. operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime end date (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None. wind_farm_restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the wind farm level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable
Reference wind farm operational data variable metadata.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the data variable. This is currently free text but should be replaced by a list of enum options. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. data_level (OperationalDataLevel(StrEnum)): Whether the operational data variable is provided for each individual wind turbine ('turbine_level'), is aggregated at the wind farm level ('wind_farm_level') or corresponds to a different ('other') unit such as an environmental measurement station. statistic_types (list[StatisticType(StrEnum)]): A list of the types of statistics included for this data variable. measurement_point (Optional[str]): Optional clarification of the point of measurement, such as the location of the energy meter for metered production. Default is None. raw_data_recovery_rate (Optional[list[Result]]): Dimensionless raw data recovery rate for the variable. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.report_metadata.Organisation
Issuing or receiving organisation of an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Entity name of the organisation. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Abbreviated name of the organisation. Default is None. address (Optional[str]): Address of the organisation. Default is None. contact_name (Optional[str]): Name(s) of contact person(s) in the organisation. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.OperationalRestriction
Specifications of a restriction that limits power output.
In the current draft of the schema, 'label', 'description' and 'comments' fields are available to describe the restriction with free text. This is intended to be expanded into a more comprehensive data model.
Attributes: label (str): Short label to indicate the type of operational restriction. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.TurbineConfiguration
Specification of all details for a turbine configuration.
Attributes: turbine_id (Optional[str]): Unique identifier of the turbine specification. Default is None. label (str): Label of the turbine. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. location (Location): The horizontal spatial location of the turbine. hub_height (float): The hub height of the turbine. turbine_model_id (str): Unique identifier of the turbine model. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the turbine level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.result.Result
Set of results for an element of an energy assessment.
Attributes: quantity (Optional[ResultsQuantity(StrEnum)]): The quantity that the set of results describe, where this is not obvious from the context. Default is None. label (Optional[str]): Label of the results. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. assessment_period (Optional[AssessmentPeriod(StrEnum)]): Period of or in time that has been assessed and for which the results are applicable. Default is None. dimensions (Optional[tuple[ResultsDimension(StrEnum), ...]]): Dimensions along which the results are binned (all result values in the same results object must have the same dimensions). Default is None. statistics (list[ResultStatistic]): List of result statistic objects that each include result values for a specific statistic type.

eya_def_tools.data_models.result.ResultStatistic
Result values for one specific statistic type.
Attributes: description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. statistic_type (StatisticType(StrEnum)): Type of statistic in the results component. values (UnionType[float, list[tuple[tuple[UnionType[float, int, str], ...], float]]]): Result as a single number or values at coordinates.

eya_def_tools.data_models.spatial.Location
Specification of a horizontal location in space.
Attributes: location_id (Optional[str]): Unique identifier of the location. Default is None. label (Optional[str]): Label of the location. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Description of the data object. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Comments on the data object. Default is None. x (float): Location x-coordinate (typically easing). y (float): Location y-coordinate (typically northing).
